# Adding Friends

When running Xeres, you definitely need to connect to some friends. Either try with someone online, but if you’re in a hurry, you can also use an automated [ChatServer](https://retroshare.ch/).

The main concept is to exchange IDs. You give your ID to your friend, and your friend gives his ID to you. Only if you do this exchange, you can connect.

You can do that directly from the main dashboard. Press the clipboard button at the right of your ID to make it ready to be pasted to your friends. To add your friend, press the Add Peer button.

![Add Peer Button](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

This will bring the following window where you can paste your friend’s ID.

Once those 2 steps are done, the software will connect directly and securely, without using any 3rd party or server.

This will bring you the following window:

![Adding Friend](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

And don't forget to give your own ID to your friend!
